          Beaches &amp Sports
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p><a href="http://www.spain.info/en_US/que-quieres/destinos-playa/playas/coruna_a/riazor.html"><b>Playa de Riazor</b></a></p>
          <p>La Coruña's most famous beach, located on the west side of the peninsula.  Beware, the water in this area of Spain is very cold despite its appearance.  The sun will be out until around 9pm at the beginning of September.</p>
          <br>
          <p><a href="http://www.stadiumguide.com/riazor/"><b>Estadio de Riazor</b></a></p>
          <p>Soccer stadium, home of Deportivo La Coruña (commonly known as Depor).  Located directly next to Riazor beach.  Soccer matches begin toward the end of August each year.  Tickets for Deportivo de La Coruña games can be bought online, by phone +34 902 43 44 43, or at the ticket windows (taquillas) of Estadio Riazor. Tickets are also available on the gate on the day of the match. Deportivo tend to have decent attendances in both the Primera and Segunda División, but rarely sell out in the latter. Ticket prices can depend on the opponent, but expect to pay between €15.00 for a lower-tier seat behind the goal and €40.00 for an upper-tier seat at the main stand.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="panel panel-default">
